STATEMENT OF PURPOSE

The laws of all jurisdictions throughout the World prohibit the enforcement of agreements that waive or otherwise limit liability for intentional, willful or grossly negligent conduct, or for any liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence. Because Creative Commons relies on your actions to affirm the limited waiver and disclaimer of liability in the license, Creative Commons needs to ensure that you have the opportunity to review the terms and conditions of this license and affirm that you know and understand this waiver and disclaimer of liability before you are able to accept the license and perform your obligations under it. By accepting this license and performing your obligations under it, you affirm that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this license, including the limited waiver and disclaimer of liability.

The Limited Public Domain Dedication below formally and irrevocably transfers all of your right, title, and interest in the Work to the public domain, to the fullest extent permitted by law, and thereby dedicates the Work to the public domain under the terms of the CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication.

LIMITED PUBLIC DOMAIN DEDICATION

The Work is dedicated to the public domain under the terms of the CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication. By executing this document, the Dedicator makes the following declarations:

1. Copyright Status. The Dedicator makes this dedication for the benefit of the public at large and to the detriment of the Dedicator's heirs and successors. The Dedicator intends this dedication to be an overt act of relinquishment in perpetuity of all present and future rights under copyright law, whether vested or contingent, in the Work. The Dedicator understands that such relinquishment of all rights includes the beneficial use of the Work, including all commercial use, public display, public performance, and reproduction of all or any portion of the Work, and the Dedicator waives any moral rights that may exist in the Work.

2. Copyright License. To the extent that any rights in the Work are not waived or dedicated to the public domain under applicable law, the Dedicator hereby irrevocably transfers all right, title, and interest in the Work to the public, to the fullest extent permitted by law, and irrevocably licenses the Work under the Creative Commons Zero 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication. The Dedicator acknowledges that the Work may have been created in part using materials or information in the public domain or that were otherwise provided by a third party. The Dedicator represents and warrants that the Dedicator has the right to make this dedication and that the Work does not violate any third-party rights.

3. Disclaimer of Warranties. The Work is provided "as is" without any warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. The Dedicator makes no representations or warranties regarding the Work's accuracy, completeness, or usefulness.

4. Limitation of Liability. In no event shall the Dedicator be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential damages (including, but not limited to, procurement of substitute goods or services; loss of use, data, or profits; or business interruption) however caused and on any theory of liability, whether in contract, strict liability, or tort (including negligence or otherwise) arising in any way out of the use of the Work, even if advised of the possibility of such damage.

5. No Endorsement. The Dedicator does not endorse or approve the Work or any use of the Work. The Dedicator makes no representation or warranty that the Work is suitable for any particular purpose or use.

6. No Affiliation. The Dedicator is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to Creative Commons or any other organization. The Dedicator's use of the Creative Commons marks does not imply any affiliation with or endorsement by Creative Commons.

This dedication is irrevocable and perpetual. The Work may be used by anyone for any purpose, including commercial purposes, without permission from the Dedicator.

